<plot>Lili St. Cyr, "the First Lady of Burlesque,' essays her own version of the Cinderella tale. Standing before a background of Cinderella scenes, Miss St. Cyr pantomime's her way through her chores, wearing a shaggy dress, until the wand of a fairy godmother transforms it into a beautiful ball-costume. At the palace she falls in love with Prince Charming but, as the clock begins to strike midnight, her magnificent garments disappear.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?106427</url></doc>
